	<h2>By car</h2>
<p><strong>To the church:</strong></p>
<p><a href="/pages/the-day">All Saints' Church</a> is on the corner of Onslow Gardens and Addington Road, on the A2022, in Sanderstead. There is a car park beside the church and free parking in nearby roads.</p>
<p><strong>To the reception:</strong></p>
<p>To get from the church to the reception by car:</p>
<ol>
<li>From the church turn left onto Addington Road, go straight across the roundabout onto Rectory park, and continue until the traffic lights with the A22.</li>
<li>Follow the A22 north towards Purley, and immediately after going through the traffic lights beside Tesco, bear left onto the A23 heading south to Coulsdon.</li>
<li>Continue on the A23 through Coulsdon to the Coulsdon by-pass, under the bridge and, after a bit, go straight across the roundabout.</li>
<li>After 2.1 miles, having gone through Hooley, keep in the right-hand lane of the dual carriageway to avoid the M23 /M25, and continue on the A23 towards Redhill.</li>
<li>After a further 2.5 miles, having gone through Merstham and a set of traffic lights, turn right at the Total garage onto the A242, Gatton Park Road towards Reigate</li>
<li>At the traffic lights at the T junction, turn right onto the A25 towards Reigate.</li>
<li>At the odd sculpture by the Esure building follow the one-way system through Reigate town centre, staying on the A25 towards Dorking. After 2.2 miles, and the second sign for Buckland, youâ€™ll see a keep left bollard, a pond to your right and a church to your left.</li>
<li>Turn left immediately into Old Road. After half a mile turn left into Sandy Lane, then immediately right into Hartsfield Manor.</li>
<li>Drive past the main house, there is car park on the right.</li>
</ol>
