	<h2>Public Transport</h2>
<p><strong>To the church:</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>The nearest railway stations to All Saints' Church are Sanderstead, Purley Oaks and Riddlesdown. The church is approx 1.3 miles (uphill) from each of them. The 403 bus route runs close to Sanderstead station, and is 1/4 mile from Purley Oaks. The 412 bus route runs 1/4 mile from Riddlesdown station. Both routes stop close to All Saints' Church.</p>
<p>For more information, and directions from other locations in London, see&nbsp;<a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/">http://www.tfl.gov.uk/</a>.</p>
<p><strong>To the reception:</strong></p>
<p>Guests are invited to reserve a seat on the coach travelling to the reception after the ceremony (see below).</p>
<p><strong>Home from the reception:</strong></p>
<p>Betchworth railway station is approx 1 mile from Hartsfield manor. This is a local station on the line between Reading and Redhill, with a relatively infrequent service. Regular train services are available to London from Dorking (3.4 miles away) and Redhill (5.1 miles away). Please ask at the hotel reception if you would like to order a taxi.</p>
